On Wednesday evening, bad weather delayed six trains on the railway
06 Nov 2019, 20:15 by Alexey Gromov

Specialists of the October Railway continue to restore the train schedule, which was violated due to adverse weather conditions on November 5 and 6. However, six trains are still delayed.

Specialists of the October Railway continue to restore the train schedule, which was violated due to adverse weather conditions on November 5 and 6. This was told in the press service of the Railways.
It is noted that the train schedule is gradually normalizing. Currently, the following trains are lagging behind:
No. 22 Petersburg - Murmansk - about five hours;
No. 819 Petrozavodsk - Pskov - more than two hours;
No. 77 Vorkuta - Petersburg - more than an hour;
No. 16 Murmansk - Moscow - about an hour;
No. 217 Petrozavodsk - Sortavala - about half an hour;
No. 9 Arkhangelsk - Petersburg - about half an hour.
The press service said that the railway dispatching apparatus was taking the necessary measures to reduce the backlog of these trains and minimize the time delays on arrival at the destination station.
In the morning, NEVSKY NEWS wrote that the Oktyabrskaya Railway eliminates the consequences after bad weather with special equipment - vibropantographs that remove ice from the wires. On the afternoon of November 6, it was reported that due to bad weather seven trains were being delayed.
